\begin_layout Chapter
List and Numbering
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Especially in the natural sciences,
 it is often useful to use a list or numbering instead of a long continuous text.
 Lists serve:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
to improve clarity
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
to provide structure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
to mention various points when no specific order can be determined.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Numbering is used when a specific order can be defined.
 As an example,
 the five safety rules of electrical engineering are listed below:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Disconnect completely
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Secure against reconnection
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
verify the absence of voltage
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Ground and short-circuit
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Cover or isolate adjacent live parts.
\end_layout

