\begin_layout Chapter
Notes on the bibliography with Biblatex
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With LaTeX/LyX,
 a bibliography can be created with or without the Biblatex system.
 The literary sources from the database are included in the bibliography of the PDF document if references to these sources are made in the text.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
References are discussed here as an example.
 A good start to the topic of 
\begin_inset Quotes grd
\end_inset

academic writing
\begin_inset Quotes grd
\end_inset

 is provided in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "kuehtz2011biblatex"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 When citing internet sources,
 it is important to use permanent links.
 For example,
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Wikipediaelektrotechnikbiblatex"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 refers to the Wikipedia article on electrical engineering.
 Here is a citation of the SI System brochure 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "sisystem"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 a literature source that is accessible online.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If you are using Biblatex,
 create a text file with the .bib extension.
 The following source code shows an example of the contents of a bib file:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

@online{sisystem,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

author		 =	{International Bureau of Weights and Measures (BIPM)},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

title		 =	{{The International System of Units (SI)}},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

date		 =   {2029-11-11},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

url			 =	{https://www.bipm.org/documents/20126/41483022/SI-Brochure-9.pdf/fcf090b2-04e6-88cc-1149-c3e029ad8232?version=4.0&t=1736179646242&download=true},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

doi	         =   {},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

organization =  {},
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

note		 =	{},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

notiz		 =	{Interne Notizen},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

subtitle     =   {},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

titleaddon   =   {},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

language     = {},
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

version      = {9th edition,
 2019},
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

addendum     = {},
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

pubstate = {}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Typically,
 the following data fields are populated:
 author,
 title,
 date (this is the date of the last access),
 url,
 and version (this is the version number and the year of publication).
 The following fields are optional:
 doi,
 organization,
 note,
 note (internal notes about the source can be entered here,
 which will not appear in the bibliography),
 subtitle,
 title addon,
 language,
 addendum,
 pubstate.
\end_layout

